I/O structure 155 At least one I/O feature (FICON) or one coupling link feature (ICA SR or CE LR) must be present in the minimum configuration. The following features can be shared and spanned:  FICON channels that are defined as FC or FCP  OSA-Express features that are defined as OSC, OSD, or OSE  Coupling links that are defined as CS5 or CL5  HiperSockets that are defined as IQD The following features are plugged into a PCIe+ I/O drawer and do not require the definition of a CHPID and CHPID type:  Each Crypto Express (8S/7S/6S) feature occupies one I/O
